Program: Outlook
Title: The dentist delivering babies in Syria
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04tkf8t
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 1 Mar 2017
Mohammed Darwish is running an underground clinic in Madaya, a town under siege in Syria. Alice Glenn from Melbourne started No Lights, No Lycra, the living room nightclub craze that's now sweeping the world. Mandy Harvey is a jazz singer from Colorado who lost her hearing as a teenager. Wang Yan owned a steel factory in Changchun, but when his pet dog went missing he was inspired to change his life. (Picture: The Syrian town of Madaya. Photo credit: Louai Beshara/AFP/Getty Images.) Show less